LightRAG~\citep{lightrag} and FastGraphRAG~\citep{fast-graphrag} eliminate community summarization: LightRAG directly extracts low- and high-level nodes from each chunk, while FastGraphRAG leverages PageRank for query-time aggregation.
\update{Youtu-GraphRAG~\cite{youtugraphrag} further reduces aggregating token usage by replacing community summarization with the selection of key entities for each community.}
However, these methods still rely on LLMs to produce structured outputs.
\update{Another line of work uses graphs primarily as a lightweight retrieval scaffold rather than an explicit global semantic representation. HippoRAG~\citep{hipporag} and HippoRAG2~\citep{hipporag2} construct sparse entity–relation graphs and apply PageRank-style propagation to reweight query-relevant entities, improving retrieval with limited indexing overhead, but they do not perform community-level summarization and thus provide weaker corpus-level global semantics; moreover, they still rely on LLM-based extraction. Building upon HippoRAG2, LinearRAG~\citep{linearrag} replaces LLM extraction with smaller models and integrates graph signals via GNNs, yet the final evidence remains chunk-centric, making it closer to a graph-enhanced text-based RAG pipeline than a fully global graph-reasoning approach.}

这里我想修改一下，让这两条line更清晰，应该是：
第一条line是仍旧从文本中抽取包含丰富语义信息，即带有description的图；第二条line是指抽取实体和关系，然后用这个图来辅助检索，即不带有description的图，第一条line有lightrag，fastgraphrag，以及Youtu GraphRAG，第二条line是HippoRAG，HippoRAG2，以及LinearRAG
